venue.address_1: Route 110 at the West Boylston / Sterling border
venue.name: Gate 33 Wachusett Reservoir

item.description: The Wachusett reservoir is home to a wide array of central New England flora and fauna.  This is a one and a half / two hour hike round trip.  We will stop and take a break on the rock outcrop overlooking the cove.  The terrain is varied but mostly an easy walk depending on your experience and fitness level.  Dress for the weather and summer insects.
item.name: Hike to Prescott Cove
